<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Export options for the Developer-ID `.dmg` channel (lifecycle stage 2.5 —
direct download from bristlenose.app, NOT the App Store). Used by
desktop/scripts/build-dmg.sh.

Contrast with ExportOptions.plist (the App Store sibling):

  method=developer-id  — targets direct distribution outside the App Store.
  Output is a standalone `.app` (not a `.pkg`). notarytool ACCEPTS this cert
  family (Developer ID Application) and REJECTS Apple Distribution — the exact
  inverse of the App Store path, which is validated server-side and never
  touches notarytool. build-dmg.sh notarises + staples the exported `.app`,
  then wraps it in a notarised+stapled `.dmg`.

  signingStyle=automatic (+ build-dmg.sh passes -allowProvisioningUpdates) —
  this app is sandboxed AND carries the Keychain Sharing (keychain-access-groups)
  entitlement, which Xcode gates behind a provisioning profile. A manual
  Developer-ID archive with an empty profile fails "requires a provisioning
  profile" — and it's the *capability* it gates on, not the $(AppIdentifierPrefix)
  variable (hardcoding the Team-ID prefix doesn't help; automatic signing only
  does *development*). Both verified dead ends, 16 Jul 2026. Automatic +
  -allowProvisioningUpdates has Xcode MINT a Developer ID provisioning profile on
  the fly (no portal trip) and embed it. So there's no signingCertificate key
  (automatic resolves the Developer ID Application cert from the team) and no
  installerSigningCertificate (Developer ID ships a `.dmg`, not a `.pkg`).
  build-dmg.sh archives with development signing first, then this plist re-signs
  as Developer ID at export; `codesign --verify --deep --strict` on the export is
  the gate that confirms the result.

  teamID Z56GZVA2QB — Bristlenose / Martin Storey.

  uploadSymbols=false — PyInstaller strips the sidecar symbols; Swift dSYMs
  stay in the .xcarchive.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>method</key>
    <string>developer-id</string>
    <key>teamID</key>
    <string>Z56GZVA2QB</string>
    <key>signingStyle</key>
    <string>automatic</string>
    <key>destination</key>
    <string>export</string>
    <key>uploadSymbols</key>
    <false/>
</dict>
</plist>
